  "description": "Tropical perennial vine from Basellaceae, native to Malabar Coast of India. Produces succulent, heart-shaped leaves and edible red berries; extremely heat- and humidity-tolerant. Cultivated throughout Indian subcontinent (Bengali, Odia, Andhra, Gujarati cuisines) and tropical Asia. Twining habit; climbing 3–6 meters per season.",
